By the chain rule,

\begin{align*}
\frac{dy}{dx} = \frac{1}{f(2x)}f'(2x)\cdot 2
\end{align*} When $x=1,$ this is
equal to

\begin{align*}
\frac{1}{f(2)}f'(2)\cdot 2 =\frac{1}{3} (-5)\cdot 2 = -\frac{10}{3}.
\end{align*}
Hence, the slope of the tangent line at $x=1$ is equal to $-10/3.$

